This category of Benenefits describes a range of advantages and improvements related to the design, construction, and functionality of buildings. These benefits include efficient screening, enhanced building design and infrastructure, increased in-service life of buildings, enhanced occupant comfort, faster construction, reduced disruption, improved thermal comfort, flexible design for versatile use of spaces, maintaining pressure differentials, improved building performance, increased options for sustainability, insulation of private sphere from communal sphere, accurate assessment of situations, improved flexibility and agility, enhanced balcony features, improved thermal insulation, flexible lighting design, versatile interior design, adaptive design approach, improved sleep quality, increased safety and flexibility in interior spaces, and maintaining physical distancing. These benefits suggest that the individuals in this list are associated with green buildings and sustainable infrastructure, with an emphasis on occupant comfort, energy efficiency, flexibility, adaptability, and improved health and safety.